The Herald Farirai Machivenyika Senior Reporter Newly elected Pan African Parliament president, Chief Fortune Charumbira has returned this afternoon following his election to the post in South Africa last week. <img class="size-full wp-image-627953" src="https://www.herald.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2022/07/273A4840.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="380" srcset="https://www.herald.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2022/07/273A4840.jpg 680w, https://www.herald.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2022/07/273A4840-360x200.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /> Chief Fortune Charumbira being welcomed at Robert Mugabe International Airport Chief Charumbira was met by Zanu PF’s Chief Whip Cde Pupurai Togarepi, Cde Tatenda Mavetera who was also elected as a member of PAP’s youth caucus and family members. <img class="size-full wp-image-627951 aligncenter" src="https://www.herald.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2022/07/273A4930.jpgchie.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="380" srcset="https://www.herald.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2022/07/273A4930.jpgchie.jpg 680w, https://www.herald.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2022/07/273A4930.jpgchie-360x200.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" />
Chief Charumbira attributed his victory to the support he got from President Mnangagwa, Zimbabweans and Africa at large. <img class="size-full wp-image-627947 aligncenter" src="https://www.herald.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2022/07/unnamed-file.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="380" srcset="https://www.herald.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2022/07/unnamed-file.jpg 680w, https://www.herald.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2022/07/unnamed-file-360x200.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" />
He pledged to pursue a development agenda for the continent.